Assets Disposal Communications Equipment Amount
The value of proceeds from the disposal of communications equipment.
Communications equipment includes modems, phones, switchboards, cable or wire for communication purposes, satellite equipment, television and radio transmitters and radio transceivers.
Assets Disposal Computer Hardware Amount
The value of proceeds from the disposal of computer hardware.
Computer hardware includes laptops, tablets, PCs, printers, mainframes and servers.
Assets Disposal Computer Software Amount
The value of proceeds from the disposal of computer software assets, purchased from another business or organisation, or developed in house by own employees.
Assets Disposal Electronic Equipment Electrical Machinery Amount
The value of proceeds from the disposal of electronic equipment and electrical machinery.
Electronic equipment and electrical machinery includes power generating equipment, transformers, batteries, solar panels and security equipment.
Assets Disposal Industrial Machinery Equipment Amount
The value of proceeds from the disposal of specialised industrial machinery or any other specialised equipment used for the operations of a business or organisation.

Specialised industrial machinery or equipment includes forklifts, conveyers, pumps, compressors, processing machinery or any other specialised equipment used for the operations of a business or organisation.
Assets Disposal Plant Equipment Other Amount
The value of proceeds from the disposal of other plant, equipment and machinery not collected elsewhere.
Assets Disposal Road Vehicles Amount

The value of proceeds from the disposal of road vehicles includes any types of vehicles where the primary use is to be driven on public roads (e.g. cars, trucks, utes or any other vehicle where the primary use is to be driven on public roads).
Assets Disposal Total Amount
The total value of proceeds from disposal of all relevant assets.
Assets Disposal Transport Equipment Other Than Road Vehicles Amount
The value of proceeds from the disposal of transport vehicles and equipment used in the transportation of people or goods, other than vehicles where the primary use is to be driven on public roads.
Transport vehicles and equipment (other than road vehicles) includes vehicles such as trailers, boats, ships, trains and aircraft.
Assets Inventories Corrected Total Amount
The corrected amount provided if the value of inventories total is different from automatically totalled amount.
Assets Property Plant And Equipment Depreciating Assets Effective Life Recalculation Indicator
Indicates whether the effective life of any depreciating assets has been recalculated by the taxpayer in the income year.

A choice of TRUE/FALSE values. true = The taxpayer has recalculated the effective life of any of their depreciating assets in the income year. false = The taxpayer has not recalculated the effective life of any of their depreciating assets in the income year.
Assets Property Plant And Equipment Depreciating Assets First Deducted Self Assessed Effective Life Indicator
Indicates whether the taxpayer has chosen to work out the effective life any depreciating assets (self-assessed).

A choice of TRUE/FALSE values. true = The taxpayer has self-assessed the effective life of any of their depreciating assets. false = The taxpayer has adopted the Commissioner's effective life determination for all their depreciating assets.
Capital Expenditure Capital Work Other Amount

The capital expenditure on goods and materials used to develop and build an asset, including services such as invoiced amounts to contractors and subcontractors, other than capitalised wages and salaries.
Capital Expenditure Computer Software Developed In House Amount
The value of capital expenditure for computer software developed in house by employees of this business or organisation.
Capital Expenditure Computer Software Purchased From Another Organisation Amount
The value of capital expenditure for computer software purchased from another business or organisation (including labour hire and consultancy costs).
Capital Expenditure Corrected Total Amount
The corrected amount provided if actual capital expenditure total is different from automatically totalled amount.
Capital Expenditure New Buildings and Other Structures Actual Amount
The amount of actual capital expenditure on new buildings and other structures.

This includes industrial and commercial buildings, houses, flats, home units, water and sewerage installations, lifts, heating, ventilating and similar equipment forming an integral part of buildings and structures, land development and construction site development, roads, bridges, wharves, harbours, railway lines, pipelines, power and telephone lines. It also includes mine development (e.g. construction of shafts in underground mines, preparation of mining and quarrying sites for open cut extraction and other developmental operations primarily for commencing or extending production). It excludes purchases of land, previously occupied buildings and speculatively built projects intended for sale before occupation.
Capital Expenditure New Buildings And Other Structures Actual Largest Value Description
The description of assets with the largest value, or values, of actual capital expenditure on new buildings and other structures.

This includes industrial and commercial buildings, houses, flats, home units, water and sewerage installations, lifts, heating, ventilating and similar equipment forming an integral part of buildings and structures, land development and construction site development, roads, bridges, wharves, harbours, railway lines, pipelines, power and telephone lines. It also includes mine development (e.g. construction of shafts in underground mines, preparation of mining and quarrying sites for open cut extraction and other developmental operations primarily for commencing or extending production). It excludes purchases of land, previously occupied buildings and speculatively built projects intended for sale before occupation.
Capital Expenditure New Buildings and Other Structures Expected Amount
The amount of expected capital expenditure on new buildings and other structures.

This includes industrial and commercial buildings, houses, flats, home units, water and sewerage installations, lifts, heating, ventilating and similar equipment forming an integral part of buildings and structures, land development and construction site development, roads, bridges, wharves, harbours, railway lines, pipelines, power and telephone lines. It also includes mine development (e.g. construction of shafts in underground mines, preparation of mining and quarrying sites for open cut extraction and other developmental operations primarily for commencing or extending production). It excludes purchases of land, previously occupied buildings and speculatively built projects intended for sale before occupation.
Capital Expenditure New Buildings And Other Structures Expected Largest Value Description
The description of assets with the largest value, or values, of expected capital expenditure on new buildings and other structures.

This includes industrial and commercial buildings, houses, flats, home units, water and sewerage installations, lifts, heating, ventilating and similar equipment forming an integral part of buildings and structures, land development and construction site development, roads, bridges, wharves, harbours, railway lines, pipelines, power and telephone lines. It also includes mine development (e.g. construction of shafts in underground mines, preparation of mining and quarrying sites for open cut extraction and other developmental operations primarily for commencing or extending production). It excludes purchases of land, previously occupied buildings and speculatively built projects intended for sale before occupation.
Capital Expenditure New Or Imported Assets Actual Amount
The amount of actual capital expenditure on brand new or imported assets.

This includes plant, machinery, vehicles, electrical apparatus, office equipment, furniture, fixtures and fittings not forming an integral part of buildings, durable containers, special tooling, etc.; also includes goods imported for the first time, whether previously used outside Australia or not; and has an expected productive life of one year or more.
Capital Expenditure New Or Imported Assets Actual Largest Value Description
The description of assets with the largest value, or values, of actual capital expenditure on brand new or imported vehicles, plant, machinery, equipment and furniture assets.

This includes plant, machinery, vehicles, electrical apparatus, office equipment, furniture, fixtures and fittings not forming an integral part of buildings, durable containers, special tooling, etc.; also includes goods imported for the first time, whether previously used outside Australia or not; and has an expected productive life of one year or more.
Capital Expenditure New Or Imported Assets Expected Amount
The amount of expected capital expenditure on brand new or imported assets.

This includes plant, machinery, vehicles, electrical apparatus, office equipment, furniture, fixtures and fittings not forming an integral part of buildings, durable containers, special tooling, etc.; also includes goods imported for the first time, whether previously used outside Australia or not; and has an expected productive life of one year or more.
Capital Expenditure New Or Imported Assets Expected Largest Value Description
The description of assets with the largest value, or values, of expected capital expenditure on brand new or imported vehicles, plant, machinery, equipment and furniture assets.

This includes plant, machinery, vehicles, electrical apparatus, office equipment, furniture, fixtures and fittings not forming an integral part of buildings, durable containers, special tooling; also includes goods imported for the first time, whether previously used outside Australia or not; and has an expected productive life of one year or more.
